		<tr>
			<td align="left" valign="top" background="/images/necrotableheader1.gif">
				<font width="100%" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white><b>Soloing In The Katta Castellum Graveyard</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="black">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white>
				written by <b>Zenatal</b> on <b>3/24/2003 8:19:52 AM</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#37437B">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color=white><blockquote><br>
				First, make your way to the graveyard. Make a pet, and park him on the path, halfway between the building and the courtyard. Now, there are a total of 7 Legionnaires that spawn in the courtyard. Looking out into the courtyard, from the Graveyard, there are 2 to your right, 2 straight ahead, and 2 to your left. The other is a roaming Legionnaire that spawns on the right hand side, in the far corner. Here's the strategy.<br><br>First:<br>Get SoW potions, Jboots, or something that will increase your speed, because you'll need it these guys are fast. <br><br>Second:<br>Cast Lich on yourself. (You'll probably never want to take it off. because you'll be constantly pulling)<br>Slowly come from the graveyard, and walk towards the first Legionnaire on your left. He will be out of aggro range of all the other Lego's. Get close enough to aggro him, and run back to your pet in the graveyard. Run past your pet, turn and cast Dooming Darkness, while your casting, have your pet attack the Lego(this is important, because if your spell doesn't stick, or your pet doesn't get to him in time you're going to get hit for upwards of 300+ damage)<br><br>Once Darknessed, and Pet is on him, Cast Fear, Then let your pet beat on him. Cast BoD on him after you fear, sit and wait for him to get around approximately 58% health. Stand, cast fear 1 more time. Your pet should kill him by the time Fear wears off the second time. If not, Fear again, and Dooming as needed.<br><br>1st guard down. <br><br>As soon as the first guard is down, run back up to the front of the graveyard. Here is a lesson in Feign Death Pulling. Get within spell range of the closest Lego on your right. Cast Dooming on him, Both will aggro if you're under level 54, 55+ you don't have to worry, you can single pull. As soon as the second guard that aggroed gets halway to you, start to cast Feign Death. You'll Feign Death, and the un Darknessed Lego will walk back to his post, and the other will stay put. Wait till the other guard gets back to his spawn point, stand up, and have the guard that's darknessed follow you into the graveyard. Repeat Above Process for killing this Lego.<br><br>2nd Guard down.<br><br>Now, find the roaming guard, wherever he is. Usually he hangs out just to the right of the entrance of the graveyard, back in the corner. you want to pull him next. Just get in Aggro range, and pull him back to pet, follow above procedure to kill him.<br><br>3rd Guard down.<br><br>Now Grab the second guard on the right, and pull him back to pet. Rinse and Repeat above.<br><br>4th Guard down.<br><br>Grab the 2nd guard on the left, you'll have to go a bit past the corner he's in, to aggro him, so do that and pull back to pet. <br><br>5th Guard down.<br><br>By the time that you kill the 5th guard, the 1st guard will have spawned again, and the cycle repeats itself. The key here is to not stop pulling, and keep Lich on Always. If you want to make things interesting try pulling the two Legos at the back, using a FD pull. You may have time to pull one of them before another spawns.<br>&nbsp;<br>
			</td>
